appress-2-38-2-beta-available" href="http://wphostreviews.com/mappress-2-38-2-beta-available">http://wphostreviews.com/mappress-2-38-2-beta-available</a></p>\n<p>If you want to try the beta:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Please be sure to make a <strong>database backup </strong>of your blog (and your old version of MapPress) before you install\n<li>Don&#8217;t install it initially on a &#8216;live&#8217; web site &#8211; test it on a development site or a copy of your site first</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Please report any bugs using the </strong><a href="http://wphostreviews.com/chris-contact"><strong>contact form</strong></a><strong>. </strong>If you can, please provide a login to your test site and I&#8217;ll try to fix any issues right away.</p>\n<h2>How do I get it?</h2>\n<p>You can download the free version of the plugin from the WordPress plugin repository. Click on the &#8216;developers&#8217; tab and select version 2.38.3.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re a Pro subscriber, the new version is available for download in <a href="http://wphostreviews.com/account">your account</a>. </p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p>Before installing the plugin, make a backup of your blog and your old MapPress version. </p>\n<ol>\n<li>Download the MapPress .zip file\n<li>From the WordPress administration screen, select Plugins -&gt; Installed Plugins. Find MapPress in the plugins list and click the &#8216;Deactivate&#8217; link to deactivate it. Then click the &#8216;Delete&#8217; link to delete it.\n<li>Select the menu Plugins -&gt; Add New. Click the &#8216;Upload&#8217; link at the top of the screen\n<li>Browse to find the .zip file you downloaded, then click the &#8216;install now&#8217; button\n<li>After the plugin installs, click the &#8216;activate&#8217; link to activate it\n<li>Go to the MapPress menu and check that it shows the correct version at the top of the screen</li>\n</ol>\n<p>You&#8217;re all done! The new version should be available and working. You can repeat these same steps to reinstall and older version if needed. If there is a fatal error or a blank screen, delete the MapPress plugin directory using an FTP client to restore the site.</p>\n<h2>MapPress Changes</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed: lat/lng pois were saving with a 1-pixel viewport (should be null)</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>MapPress Pro Changes</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed: some mashup queries were not working properly\n<li>Fixed: maps based on custom fields were not generating correctly\n<li>Changed: queries now default to showing ALL matching posts (posts_per_page=-1) so it&#8217;s no longer necessary to include &#8220;posts_per_page=-1&#8243; in the query. You can still include the parameter if you <em>do</em>want to limit the returned posts, for example &#8220;posts_per_page=20&#8243;.\n<li>Changed: if no map types are selected in the settings, ALL types are displayed (including custom styles)</li>\n</ul>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:61:"http://wphostreviews.com/mappress-2-38-3-beta-available//feed";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:41:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:30:"MapPress 2.38.2 Beta Available";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:56:"http://wphostreviews.com/mappress-2-38-2-beta-available/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8